article.headline: IUPUI 103, UMKC 65
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Robert Glenn scored more than 20 points for the fourth straight time as Indiana University-Purdue University Indianapolis cruised past Missouri-Kansas City 103-65 on Thursday night. The outing was the highest scoring of the season for the Jaguars (19-9, 12-3 Summit), topping their 98-67 win over Indiana University East in November. This time out, Glenn scored 29 points and made a career-high five assists to help the Jaguars bounce back from a tough 60-61 loss on Saturday against Oral Roberts, a game in which he finished with 28 points. Alex Young helped out Thursday with 26 points while Leroy Nobles added 18 and Jon Avery had 14. LaTreze Mushatt led the Kangaroos (11-15, 5-10) in scoring with 19 points and Jay Couisnard finished with 10.
